<head>
<title>Plant A Row For The Hungry</title>
<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
</head>

<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF">

<h1><font color="#800000"><font size="6">PLANT A ROW FOR THE
HUNGRY</font></font> </h1>

<hr>

<p>With the onslaught of spring, music and gardening joined
forces with nature to announce a nationwide seed give away aimed
at giving home gardeners a hand in stopping world hunger. The
Hard Rock Café restaurant chain and Ferry-Morse international
seed distributors gave their support to the garden writors 1996
Plant a Row for the Hungry Campaign. Long time host of The
Victory Garden, Jim Wilson held a media conference in New York
City's Manhattan Hard Rock Café offering free seed packets with
a challenge to city gardeners to grow at least one row to donate.
</p>

<p>For advice and information on growing vegetables, locating
food banks and <b>to request seeds by mail</b> call Ferry-Morse
Gardener's Help Line at 1-800-283-3400. </p>

<p><font color="#800000"><b><i>Editor's Note: This challenge to
help Plant a Row for the Hungry is not limited to New York or the
US, anyone worldwide may participate. Anyone with a small piece
of land, private (i.e., residents or business) or public (i.e.,
schools, libraries, government buildings) can dedicate the
growing of a food garden to the spirit of helping others. Dig
will continue to list this number and challenge to all growers
that might wish to join in this opportunity.</i></b></font> </p>

<hr>

