<head>
<title>The Art of Earl Hubbard: Le Capitaine II</title>
<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
</head>

<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF" text="#000000" link="#FF8000"
vlink="#C0C0C0" alink="#FF0000">

<p align="center">&nbsp;</p>

<p align="center"><font color="#FF8000"><img src="captain.jpg"
align="bottom" width="289" height="400"></font></p>

<p align="center">&nbsp;Hubbard's art spans the last half of the
1900s. A hard-edge painter <br>
fascinated by the human face, he was the first living American
artist to be given <br>
a one-man show at Huntington Hartford's Gallery of Modern Art, in
Manhattan (1965)</p>

