<HEAD><TITLE>INFOTHEQUE SIDA - Infoth&egrave;que SIDA 02/96</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="FFFFFF">
<A HREF="/f/search"><IMG ALIGN=RIGHT BORDER=0 SRC="/gif/Search2.gif"></A>
<A HREF="INFOTHEQUE.cgi?+9602"><IMG ALIGN=RIGHT BORDER=0 SRC="/gif/Bibliotheque2.gif"></A><IMG ALIGN=left BORDER=0 SRC="INFOTHEQUE/gif/marge.gif"><H2>AIDS INFOTHEK - INFOTHEQUE SIDA</H2><I>Das Magazin der Aids Info Docu Schweiz<BR>Le magazine de Sida Info Doc Suisse</I><BR CLEAR><p><center><b><i>On a constat&eacute; que toute infection "consomme", c'est-&agrave;-dire que l'organisme a besoin de davantage d'&eacute;nergie, de vitamines et de min&eacute;raux. Cela vaut aussi pour l'infection par le VIH.<br>Man hat festgestellt, dass jede Infektion "konsumierend" wirkt, das heisst, der K&ouml;rper braucht mehr Energie, Vitamine und Mineralstoffe. Das gilt auch f&uuml;r die HIV-Infektion.</i></b></center><p><CENTER>
<A HREF="INFOTHEQUE.cgi?9602:12.2"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="/gif/left.gif"></A>
<A HREF="INFOTHEQUE.cgi?9602:12.4"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="/gif/right.gif"></A>
</CENTER>
<UL>
<h3>Living on the edge. Coping with HIV and drug misuse</h3><blockquote><b>AIDS and Drugs Video Consortium (Ed.), Hygia Communications (Prod.)</b><br><i>London, 1993, 38 Min., £ 55.-- (mit Begleitmaterial)</i><p>"Living on the edge" tells the stories of a number of drug users and ex-users with HIV infection filmed over a three year period. These personal insights show the range of feelings and experiences of many drug users in gaining trust, respect and services from doctors, carers and drug and HIV agencies. The video shows how gaps in understanding between DRUGS agencies on the one hand and AIDS agencies on the other can lead clients and workers feeling mutually bewildered, frustrated, unsupported and let down. The video is divided into two main parts. The first part covers issues specific to drug-users with HIV, the second shows examples of support and interaction between users and support agencies. The tape is divided into twenty numbered clips of short scenes that can be used to trigger discussion during training. These scenes are intended to be used in conjunction with the accompanying training guide.</blockquote></UL>
<HR>
<CENTER>
<A HREF="INFOTHEQUE.cgi?9602:12.2"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="/gif/left.gif"></A>
<A HREF="INFOTHEQUE.cgi?9602:12.4"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="/gif/right.gif"></A>
</CENTER>
